<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Calling strlen(token) can access memory beyond the bounds of the object pointed to by token if token is not NUL-terminated within token_len bytes. The code only checks token != NULL and token[0] != '\0' but does not guarantee a terminating '\0'. The mhd_assert macro is defined as ((void)0) (no runtime check), so the strlen call itself may read past the buffer and thus violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17 (e.g. token points to a token_len-sized buffer without a terminating NUL, strlen will scan beyond token_len).
</scenario>
